Here is the solution I got back from Microsoft:
<br />
<br />If you need an
<br />ImageButton in your GridView, the best workaround is to use a TemplateField with
<br />an ImageButton in it:
<br />
<br />&lt;asp:GridView ID="GridView1" runat="server"&gt;
<br />  &lt;Columns&gt;
<br />    &lt;asp:TemplateField&gt;
<br />      &lt;ItemTemplate&gt;
<br />        &lt;asp:ImageButton runat=server id="ImageButton1" CommandName="Delete"
<br />ImageUrl="..." CommandArgument='&lt;%# DataBinder.Eval(Container, "RowIndex") %&gt;'
<br />OnCommand="ImageButton1_Command" /&gt;
<br />      &lt;/ItemTemplate&gt;
<br />    &lt;/asp:TemplateField&gt;
<br />  &lt;/Columns&gt;
<br />&lt;/asp:GridView&gt;
